    <title>GTK+ Input Method Documentation</title>
    <summary>Better late than never. GTK+ has supported loadable input method modules since the beginning of the century. However, how to actually implement a custom input method and make GTK+ use it has never been documented.
So, if you ever wanted to implement your own GTK+ input method (say, for example, one that completes words from a [...]</summary>
    <content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>Better late than never. GTK+ has supported loadable input method modules since the beginning of the century. However, how to actually implement a custom input method and make GTK+ use it has never been documented.</p>
<p>So, if you ever wanted to implement your own GTK+ input method (say, for example, one that completes words from a dictionary like it works on a mobile phone) but have been put off by the lack of <a href="http://danielkitta.org/doc/gtk/GtkIMContext.html">GtkIMContext documentation</a> — there you go. The patch is waiting at <a href="http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=563994">bug #563994</a>, for early approvers.</p>
<p>It would be nice if there were a non-hackish way to reduce the GTK+ documentation build times, by the way…</p></div>
    </content>
