    <content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><span style="font-weight: bold;">EMail processing &amp; Desktop search</span> : Are you interested in these ? I dont have a job opening on this but instead have an interesting problem at hand and would love to receive your thoughts on it.<br/><br/>As you might already know , <a href="http://blogs.gnome.org/sragavan/">Srini</a> and I have <a href="http://psankar.blogspot.com/2008/07/project-madagascar.html">implemented sqlite based summary</a> for Evolution. With the previous summary format, Beagle was able to search evolution mails via its meta-summary approach. After on-disk summary implementation, this meta summary is no longer in use.<br/><br/>Now we need to figure out a way, by which , email meta-data (from subject etc.) can be made accessible for applications like Tracker, Beagle, Google desktop search etc. <a href="http://pvanhoof.be/blog/">Philip Vanhoof</a> started <a href="http://live.gnome.org/Evolution/Metadata">some work</a> on this and a discussion is open on the evolution-hackers and tracker-dev thread. Express your esteemed comments and opinions <a href="http://mail.gnome.org/archives/evolution-hackers/2008-December/msg00000.html"><span style="font-weight: bold;">on the thread</span></a>.</div>
