    <content type="xhtml" xml:lang="en"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>The blog post in which I talk about life, Xesam, and WinWrangler.</p>
<h3>WinWrangler 0.2</h3>
<p>As the section header implies <a href="https://launchpad.net/winwrangler">WinWrangler</a> 0.2 has been released. The highlights are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Now translatable - and the first translation is in! Thanks to <a href="http://whoisi.com/p/2309">Wouter</a>!</li>
<li>A bug breaking pretty much all WW’s functionality on Gnome &gt;= 2.24 has been fixed</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Tarball here</strong>: <a href="http://launchpad.net/winwrangler/0.2/0.2/+download/winwrangler-0.2.tar.gz">winwrangler-0.2.tar.gz</a></p>
<p><strong>PPA</strong>: <a href="https://launchpad.net/~kamstrup/+archive">launchpad.net/~kamstrup/+archive</a></p>
<p><strong>What is WinWrangler again?</strong>: <a href="http://grillbar.org/files/winwrangler-screencast-0.1.ogg">See the WinWrangler screencast from my old blog post</a></p>
<h3>Xesam</h3>
<p>I’ve been much to silent about Xesam lately, and I shall be the first to admit that we have lost a bit of momentum, however I am confident that we will get back on track. It is my sincere plan to have the 1.0 spec set in stone before Christmas. After that Xesam GLib should begin to pick up steam again.</p>
<h3>Life</h3>
<p>Now for the whining, you may skip this part <img alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" src="http://www.grillbar.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif"/> I’ve been feeling totally drained of energy lately, not just my hacking mojo, but pretty much in all aspects of life. November more or less felt like a series of events just passing by my apathic eyes. I am not really sure what hit me, but I am determined not to let it stay that way and the energies are beginning to reappear - I even took the dog for a jog tonight - and it was cold and rainy (standard danish weather)!</p></div>
    </content>
    <updated>2008-12-08T22:15:33Z</updated>
    <published>2008-12-08T22:15:33Z</published>
